nts1.d:
Known for their boundary pushing, often challenging electronic productions, and pioneering experiential live performances, the duo of Sheffield's Mark Fell and Mat Steel deviated from their city's tradition for more straightforward bleep and techno offshoots to create sparse, minimal and repetitive competitions that favour gentle insistence over high impact.
"we focus on leaving the audience feeling cold, not just a lack of interest in trying to engage anyone, but more like deliberately avoiding this… no dynamic changes in beats or nodding heads behind powerbooks, just large, awkward, immobile slabs of form. Imagine a Zen Buddhist with unresolved emotional issues. For me, thats how this particular "vibe" relates to minimal or formal aesthetics." - Mark Fell

nts1.d: Collector John Gómez brightens up Mondays with some music from different times and different places.
Sam Shepherd a.k.a Floating Points barely needs introduction. Cataloguing depths uncharted to expose some of the best jazz, soul, rare groove and disco around.
System Olympia joins us for an hour a month.

South London musician Tara Lily brings the sound of her new collaborative release with King Krule to the NTS airwaves, sharing inspirations and offcuts from the raw, jazz-inflected DIY pop of “Quiet Nights”.
Welcome to Club Coco: a place where globe-trotting vinyl hunter Coco María shares her joyous discoveries - jazz, fusion, international pop, vintage latin music of all flavours…
Tune in to the sound of SUNCUT, boasting a heartfelt selection of some favourite 45’s through to classic bonafide soulful jams.

Bolero was once termed the 'quintessential Latin American romantic song of the twentieth century', a Cuban genre originating in the late 19th century out of the trova tradition, pioneered by troubadour Pepe Sánchez. Boleros are defined by their love-themed lyrics, but musically can take a variety of forms; as such it has such been fused with a variety of other genres over time such as rumba, mambo, and chachachá - giving the genre such an enduring and timeless quality.
The boleros were originally sung by single trovadores playing guitar, but it soon became popular for trovadores to play in groups as dúos, tríos, cuartetos. After gaining global popularity, boleros paved the way for the filin movement in Havana - a word derived from feeling, describing a style of post-microphone jazz-influenced romantic song.
This Guide To covers the most romantic exitos of the genres bolero and filin, crooners for the month of love.

nts1.d: Organ Tapes and friends play disparate music plied and wrenched together with religious fervour. Sound of E5 上海 monthly on a Monday.

nts1.d: Recorded live from Naarm/Melbourne, Great Southern Lands is an excursion through the deep Australian and New Zealand underground. Expect post-VU freakouts, dolewave jangles, forgotten lathe-cuts and avant-garde chin scratchers, served up by a bunch of Antipodean amateurs.

nts2.d:
Since starting in a basement apartment in Seattle back in 2001, Light In The Attic has established itself as one of the best and brightest reissue labels around. With releases ranging from D’Angelo to Serge Gainsbourg, Lewis to Betty Davis, Sly Stone to Karen Dalton, LITA prides itself on the breadth of its output.
Artwork by: by Hiroshi Nagai
Music Supervisor and DJ Dhamirah Coombes brings a monthly multi-genre curation of m00d-bending tracks intended for a deep listening experience.

This episode is a special made from Basel, Switzerland. While I am on a residency from Pro-Helvetia, I watched for the first time an acoustic concert by Mercedes Sosa played in 1980 in Lugano, Switzerland. After being detained in 1978 while playing live in the city of La Plata, Argentina by the government during the last military coup, and receiving death threats, she exiled to France. This concert is a clear manifestation of her sadness and her longing for returning, while also expressing hope, love and faith in the wisdom of music.

8ULENTINA is an interdisciplinary artist, music producer and DJ based in Brooklyn, New York. Known for his dynamic DJ sets and music composition synthesizing a range of genres, geographies and tempos. He co-founded CLUB CHAI (2016-2021), a record label and curatorial platform with Lara Sarkissian and currently runs a SILLAGE, a platform for contemporary sonic artifacts. His NTS show explores the sounds that inspire his production process, focusing on experimentation, percussive intensity, and non linear storytelling through sound.

Sounds from the new crop of producer-led music bringing the stillness of ambient and downtempo music to rap. 
Image: Shed Theory

Berlin-based artist Pavel Milyakov aka Buttechno joins us for an hour a month.
From the host: "Accidental Meetings resident + movement specialist, marjai draws from various hyperlocal milieus, collaging the scuzzy with the high-def for minor fuckery & esoteric groove. Choice records from Ushara, nudo, & MIDEX ++"

nts2.n: Palestinian Sound Archive x Majazz Project
nts2.d:
Mo'min Swaitat teams up with some of his favourite artists and labels to present his collection of vintage cassettes from Palestine and beyond, including jazz, funk and Bedouin field recordings.
From The Host: For our end of the year NTS monthly show I will be playing vinyls, cassettes and CDs, that I have been given as gifts in my tour this year, as a thank you to everyone invited the Palestinian sound archive / Majazz project to their cities.
Clandestine record label, The Trilogy Tapes, tear up the NTS studios once a month, ripping through the grittiest and muddiest tracks. No words on this one, just tunes.
Los Angeles producer & sound artist claire rousay journeys through healing plaintive electronics, quotidian field recordings & minimalist compositions.

nts2.n: Under Sleepy Moon w/ Yawning Portal: Anywhere Mix
nts2.d:
Zzzzzzzzzzzz… Shhhh… There's a baby sleeping in the house!
From the host: "featuring influences, edits and excerpts from our debut album ‘Anywhere’"

nts2.n: Lost in the Bitrate w/ Lena Raine
nts2.d:
Video game composer Lena Raine explores sounds of digital – playing digital fusion, electronica, and modern orchestral works that blend live and digital sounds.
From the host: "This month, Lost in the Bitrate highlights some of the most exciting music being release in independent video games from 2025. From smaller obscure titles, to high profile releases, these varied sounds frame a picture of games unafraid to embrace the range of fidelity available to them."

Sarah Davachi serenades the LA airwaves once a month with Le Jardin - an amalgamation of progressive rock, acid folk, early music, experimental productions, & minimal sympathetic sounds.
From the host: "This month features a special holiday episode of early music and choral music selections, also to celebrate the 100th episode of Le Jardin."

nts2.n: Here too, where to w/ Bung
nts2.d: London alternative singer songwriter stops by the studio to share some original music from new EP "Here too, where to" as well as a mix of personal inspirations behind new release – experimental, folk, and R&B.

nts2.n: Day Care w/ DJ Randy Ellis & The Alaia of CQQL Records
nts2.d:
CQQL Records founders DJ Randy Ellis and The Alaia bring you Day Care, a 2-hour monthly afternoon curriculum of Boogie Funk, Disco, R&B, G-Funk, House, Modern Soul wax, and way way more. Expect to be powdered and pampered by these audio obsessives.
From the host: "modern soul and funk from late 70s to mid 80s"

Get to know Akito Hearnshaw - chief of the minimal club tracks. Tune in for his selections of burnt out, distorted, rhythmic movers. Bitcrushed, resonant snares clap and kicks punch…
From the host: "Osaka-based DJ Natsuki takes-over the final show of 2025"

nts2.d:
This will be the final episode for the Architects program. Much love and respect to the NTS family and the listeners that have been tuning into my show since the first episode back in May 2017. 
To bookend Architects I’ve decided to showcase the talents of one of my all time favorite artists. He continues to inspire me and I'm grateful to have spent some time with him over the last couple of years. Please enjoy this selection of tunes from André 3000

High Jazz* is an independent record label specializing in 70s & 80s soul, jazz & funk. ill Dubio takes the reigns for the monthly High Jazz* show rustling up an hour of choice selections on a Wednesday.

Two hours of idiosyncratic and deeply personal dub and reggae recordings from one of the Jamaica's most unique and misunderstood talents, Keith Hudson. 
Selected and mixed by JD Twitch.
"Shakshouka" is a dialectal arabic word used in North Africa to reflect an unexpected mixture of elements that wouldn’t naturally go together.

subtle.d: In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.

subtle.n: THE CULTURE HEAD w. SAINT VOX

subtle.d: DIGDIS presents a selection of tracks that captures the vibrant and ever-evolving edges of dance music. Each show features a wide range of music that can be enjoyed both on the dancefloor and in more intimate listening spaces.

My show focuses on percussive, club sounds, taking inspiration from the edges of drill, funky and bass music. In both my mixes and productions, I like to keep the energy high and a little whimsical. Expect some moments of ambient and R&B too, just so we can all catch our breath.
With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

Jedah started DJ'ing at the tender age of 18 years of age specialising in UK Garage/Grime. 

Jedah is currently the DJ for Grime Original Hollowman Jendor of the former Grime Collective Essentials/ OG's.

Responsible for “that massive grime tune with the Psycho strings”, UK producers/DJs Trends & Boylan are well versed in what the scene has to offer. They use this platform to showcase music from across the 140 spectrum from Grime to Dubstep. Anything goes!!

XOSÉ is a DJ and aspiring producer mixing and making mostly UK Garage, Grime and UK Funky. FORWARD PRESSURE largely focuses on the aforementioned UK born genres, though you can expect a variety of UK influenced sounds.

Sempra is a producer & DJ based in London, specialising in the fusion of UK Garage, Jungle and Breakbeat with dreamy vocal melodies and the beautiful instrumentation found in Soul and contemporary RnB. Sempra’s consistent output has been released by labels such as Future Classic and Headroom, gaining industry support from the likes of Nia Archives, Sherelle, Yung Singh and Dr Dubplate.

Cicely is a northern raised London based music photographer and DJ. From learning to mix during lockdown, she has since played at clubs across the country in venues such as Fabric, Corsica and Fold.

Cicely runs a collective and events night under the name NRG CRU which focus heavily on the high energy rave sound. She is highly influenced by the northern sound she grew up with, and you can hear this within her sets. Expect heavy blends of techno and hardcore while she shines the light on her favourite northern artists.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Vinyl DJ from Leigh-on-Sea. Loves collecting records with a wide array of taste ranging from House and Techno to Grime, Dubstep and Jungle. Garage holds a special place in his heart and makes up the largest part of my collection and DJ sets.

DJ & Producer hailing from Watford influenced by Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Grime with releases on NSX records & Ghost Phone, spinning electronic genres from R&B edits, Drum and Bass and everything in between.
Highlander brings you 2 hours of the freshest Jungle, Hardcore, Dubstep and Breaks. 3rd Saturday 7-9pm lock in!

subtle.n: What's The Weather, Selecta? w/ Megan Wroe

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

Wheel2Wheel is a Manchester based event which primarily focuses on the underground sectors to genres such as UK Garage, House, Tech House, Electro, Minimal and Breakbeat. Co-Founder Freddie SJ hosts the first hour of the show, sharing his favourites as well as recent digs across the genres, and then invites fellow friends, artists and nights from the scene to present hour-long guest mixes which aims to shine a light on their sound and who they are!


With hours of Discogs screen-time under his belt and a passion for 90's & early 00's releases, expect to hear a variety of different tunes from Labels you may have never heard of and Countries you might not expect!


Give us a follow on Instagram to hear about our upcoming events and all other things music related! @wheel2wheel.mcr

Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
